   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m001\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Basket Affinity Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Project Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This notebook analyzes transaction baskets to discover which products are frequently bought together. We use co-occurrence analysis and association-style metrics to generate merchandising and cross-selling recommendations.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Build product co-occurrence matrices from transaction data.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Calculate support, confidence, and lift metrics for product pairs.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Identify actionable product affinities for bundling and recommendations.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Visualize product relationships with heatmaps and network-style charts.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Business / Research Problem\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Retailers want to understand which products are naturally purchased together to optimize shelf placement, bundle offers, and recommendation engines.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Why This Analysis Matters\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Cross-selling and upselling driven by real purchase patterns consistently outperform random product suggestions. Data-driven merchandising can increase average order value by 10-30%.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m002\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Synthetic dataset of **5,000 transactions** with multiple items per basket across 20 products.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Synthetically generated for educational purposes.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m003\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Environment Setup\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c001\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for pkg in [\\\"pandas\\\", \\\"numpy\\\", \\\"matplotlib\\\", \\\"seaborn\\\"]:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    except ImportError:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        subprocess.check_call([sys.executable, \\\"-m\\\", \\\"pip\\\", \\\"install\\\", \\\"-q\\\", pkg])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Environment ready.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m004\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Imports\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c002\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import numpy as np\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import pandas as pd\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import seaborn as sns\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from itertools import combinations\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from collections import Counter\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import warnings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"warnings.filterwarnings(\\\"ignore\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.set_style(\\\"whitegrid\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"%matplotlib inline\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m005\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Configuration / Constants\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c003\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"SEED = 42\\n\",\n",
    "    \"N_TRANSACTIONS = 5000\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"PRODUCTS = [\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Bread\\\", \\\"Milk\\\", \\\"Butter\\\", \\\"Eggs\\\", \\\"Cheese\\\", \\\"Yogurt\\\", \\\"Coffee\\\", \\\"Tea\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Sugar\\\", \\\"Cereal\\\", \\\"Pasta\\\", \\\"Sauce\\\", \\\"Rice\\\", \\\"Chicken\\\", \\\"Beef\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Apples\\\", \\\"Bananas\\\", \\\"Tomatoes\\\", \\\"Onions\\\", \\\"Potatoes\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Define product affinities (pairs that go together)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"AFFINITIES = [\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (\\\"Bread\\\", \\\"Butter\\\"), (\\\"Bread\\\", \\\"Milk\\\"), (\\\"Bread\\\", \\\"Eggs\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (\\\"Coffee\\\", \\\"Sugar\\\"), (\\\"Coffee\\\", \\\"Milk\\\"), (\\\"Tea\\\", \\\"Sugar\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (\\\"Pasta\\\", \\\"Sauce\\\"), (\\\"Pasta\\\", \\\"Cheese\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (\\\"Chicken\\\", \\\"Rice\\\"), (\\\"Beef\\\", \\\"Potatoes\\\"), (\\\"Beef\\\", \\\"Onions\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (\\\"Cereal\\\", \\\"Milk\\\"), (\\\"Eggs\\\", \\\"Cheese\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (\\\"Tomatoes\\\", \\\"Onions\\\"), (\\\"Apples\\\", \\\"Bananas\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Configuration loaded.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m006\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Generation\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Each transaction contains 2-8 products. We embed known affinities to simulate realistic co-purchase patterns.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c004\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"rng = np.random.default_rng(SEED)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"baskets = []\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for i in range(N_TRANSACTIONS):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    n_items = rng.integers(2, 9)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    items = set(rng.choice(PRODUCTS, size=n_items, replace=False))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Add affinity pairs with probability\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    for a, b in AFFINITIES:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        if a in items and rng.random() < 0.55:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            items.add(b)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    baskets.append({\\\"transaction_id\\\": f\\\"T{i+1:05d}\\\", \\\"items\\\": list(items)})\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Explode into item-level rows\\n\",\n",
    "    \"rows = []\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for b in baskets:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    for item in b[\\\"items\\\"]:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        rows.append({\\\"transaction_id\\\": b[\\\"transaction_id\\\"], \\\"product\\\": item})\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df = pd.DataFrame(rows)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Total rows (item-level): {len(df):,}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Unique transactions: {df['transaction_id'].nunique():,}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Unique products: {df['product'].nunique()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df.head(10)\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m007\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Data Validation Checks\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c005\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Missing values: {df.isnull().sum().sum()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Check: no duplicate items within a transaction\\n\",\n",
    "    \"dupes = df.groupby([\\\"transaction_id\\\", \\\"product\\\"]).size().reset_index(name=\\\"cnt\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Duplicate item-in-basket: {(dupes['cnt'] > 1).sum()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"✅ Validation passed.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m008\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Exploratory Data Analysis\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c006\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"basket_sizes = df.groupby(\\\"transaction_id\\\")[\\\"product\\\"].count()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Avg basket size: {basket_sizes.mean():.1f} items\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Median basket size: {basket_sizes.median():.0f} items\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"basket_sizes.hist(bins=15, ax=axes[0], color=\\\"steelblue\\\", edgecolor=\\\"white\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_title(\\\"Basket Size Distribution\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_xlabel(\\\"Items per basket\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"product_freq = df[\\\"product\\\"].value_counts()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"product_freq.plot(kind=\\\"barh\\\", ax=axes[1], color=\\\"seagreen\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_title(\\\"Product Frequency\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m009\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Co-Occurrence Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"We compute how often each pair of products appears together in the same basket, then calculate support, confidence, and lift.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c007\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Build basket sets\\n\",\n",
    "    \"basket_sets = df.groupby(\\\"transaction_id\\\")[\\\"product\\\"].apply(set).values\\n\",\n",
    "    \"n_baskets = len(basket_sets)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Count pairs\\n\",\n",
    "    \"pair_counts = Counter()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"item_counts = Counter()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for basket in basket_sets:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    for item in basket:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        item_counts[item] += 1\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    for pair in combinations(sorted(basket), 2):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        pair_counts[pair] += 1\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Build metrics dataframe\\n\",\n",
    "    \"pair_metrics = []\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for (a, b), count in pair_counts.most_common(100):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    support_ab = count / n_baskets\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    support_a = item_counts[a] / n_baskets\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    support_b = item_counts[b] / n_baskets\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    confidence_ab = count / item_counts[a]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    confidence_ba = count / item_counts[b]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    lift = support_ab / (support_a * support_b)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    pair_metrics.append({\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"product_a\\\": a, \\\"product_b\\\": b,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"co_occurrences\\\": count,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"support\\\": round(support_ab, 4),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"confidence_a→b\\\": round(confidence_ab, 4),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"confidence_b→a\\\": round(confidence_ba, 4),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"lift\\\": round(lift, 3),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    })\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"pairs_df = pd.DataFrame(pair_metrics).sort_values(\\\"lift\\\", ascending=False)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"=== Top 15 Product Pairs by Lift ===\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"pairs_df.head(15)\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m010\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"**Interpretation:** Lift > 1 means the products are purchased together more often than random chance would predict. High-lift pairs are strong candidates for bundling, cross-selling, and shelf proximity.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m011\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Visual Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Co-occurrence heatmap for top products\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c008\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Build co-occurrence matrix\\n\",\n",
    "    \"top_products = product_freq.head(12).index.tolist()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"cooc_matrix = pd.DataFrame(0, index=top_products, columns=top_products)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for (a, b), count in pair_counts.items():\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    if a in top_products and b in top_products:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        cooc_matrix.loc[a, b] = count\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        cooc_matrix.loc[b, a] = count\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 8))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.heatmap(cooc_matrix, annot=True, fmt=\\\"d\\\", cmap=\\\"YlOrRd\\\", ax=ax, linewidths=0.5)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_title(\\\"Product Co-Occurrence Matrix (Top 12 Products)\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c009\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Top pairs by lift\\n\",\n",
    "    \"top_pairs = pairs_df.head(15)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"labels = top_pairs.apply(lambda r: f\\\"{r['product_a']} + {r['product_b']}\\\", axis=1)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"colors_bar = ['#2ecc71' if l > 1.5 else '#f39c12' if l > 1.2 else '#e74c3c' for l in top_pairs['lift']]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.barh(labels, top_pairs[\\\"lift\\\"], color=colors_bar)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.axvline(1.0, color=\\\"black\\\", ls=\\\"--\\\", alpha=0.5, label=\\\"Lift = 1 (random)\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_xlabel(\\\"Lift\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_title(\\\"Top Product Pairs by Lift\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.legend()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.invert_yaxis()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m012\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Key Findings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Pasta + Sauce has the highest lift,** confirming the strong natural recipe-driven affinity.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Bread + Butter and Coffee + Sugar** are classic high-lift pairs suitable for bundling.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Protein + starch combinations** (Chicken+Rice, Beef+Potatoes) show strong meal-level purchasing.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Cereal + Milk** confirms the breakfast category affinity.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Some pairs have high support but low lift** — these are individually popular products that appear together by chance.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m013\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Limitations\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Synthetic data with pre-engineered affinities.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- No customer-level analysis (repeat purchase patterns).\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- No price or promotion effects considered.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Binary presence only — no quantity information.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Limited to pairwise analysis; triplet+ patterns not explored.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m014\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Recommendations / Next Steps\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Bundle high-lift pairs** (Pasta+Sauce, Bread+Butter) with small discounts.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Place complementary products near each other** in store layouts.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Use in recommendation engines:** \\\"Customers who bought X also bought Y.\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Extend to triplet analysis** using the Apriori or FP-Growth algorithm.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Add seasonality:** do affinities change during holidays?\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m015\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Common Mistakes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Confusing support with lift.** High support means both products are popular; high lift means they're bought *together* more than expected.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Ignoring baseline frequency.** Milk appears in many baskets — pairing it with anything shows moderate co-occurrence, but lift may be ~1.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Acting on low-count pairs.** A pair seen 3 times with lift=5 is unreliable.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Not filtering by minimum support.** Rare pairs can have extreme lift but no practical value.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Assuming causation.** People buy bread and butter together — but promoting bread won't make people buy butter.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m016\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Mini Challenge / Exercises\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Filter pairs to those with support ≥ 5% and lift ≥ 1.3.** How many actionable pairs remain?\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Implement the Apriori algorithm** (from `mlxtend`) and compare results.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Build a product recommendation function:** given a product, return the top 3 complementary products.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Add product categories** and study inter-category vs intra-category affinities.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Simulate a bundle promotion:** if Pasta+Sauce are sold as a bundle at 10% off, estimate the revenue impact.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m017\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Final Summary / Key Takeaways\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Lift is the most useful metric** for identifying non-obvious product affinities.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Recipe and meal-level patterns drive the strongest affinities** in grocery data.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Always apply minimum support and count filters** before acting on association rules.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Basket analysis directly supports merchandising, bundling, and recommendation strategies.**\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  }\n",
    " ],\n",
